On Sun, 10 Apr 2005, Don Tuleja wrote:

> Can't a good machine shop drill a port for the vacuum advance on those 40's?

It would have to be a _very_ good shop!  Remember that the vacuum advance
isn't simply a port to vacuum.  It creates a vacuum signal from a port
very near the throttle butterfly.  Moving the port a few thousandths of an
inch would make a big differnence in the signal!

George
